content.description: It's an under cling crack with some chossy crimps up to some upper pocket with a few finger locks. The climb really tops out at a bush on the top. The crux of the route is a large side pocket to the left that you have to match (keep in mind that I'm not the tallest.)Â
content.location: It's near the end of the canyon and has two slightly far from each other bolts around a bush.

content.description: Powerful beginning to delicate upper moves.  Crux is low.
content.location: This is the obvious center route on the left side, in the wide section of canyon.  There is a 5.12 to the right of it, and there may be another route to the left.  See picture.

content.description: Smooth, juggy face to juggy arete.
content.protection: Three bolts to a single cold shut.  You may choose to sling the boulder above the anchor for toproping.
content.location: The first climb on the left after you pass the wide section of the canyon and turn a small corner.  Just past the Unknown 5.12.

content.description: Mellow staircase to steepening upper choss.
content.location: This is the first route you come to as you approach the canyon.  It is the obvious low-angle climb on your right as you walk through the wash.

content.protection: Bolts to anchors.  Stick clip recommended.
content.location: This route is on left, as the far end of the wide section of canyon.  Clean light colored overhanging section.  See photo.

content.description: Steep, hard pockets to a bat-filled, low-angle crack.  More fun than this makes it sound.
content.protection: Four or five bolts to anchors.
content.location: On the right side of the canyon, directly across from the Unknown 5.9.  Once you walk through the narrow foyer, pass through the wide section and this will be the first climb on your right.

content.description: This climb looks 5.9 and every move is a solid 10 or 11 move.  Some fun lieback moves, with slopey holds throughout.
content.location: This is one of the first climbs on the right that you come to when you walk into the foyer of the slot canyon.  It trends slightly left up a featured arete.
